Concurrency:

thread safety, is applicable to multi-threaded code. can only manipulate shared data structures in a manner that ensures that all threads behave properly. meant to fulfill design specifications without unintended interaction

goes by many names, thread safe; implementation is guaranteed to be free of race conditions when accessed by multiple threads simultaneously. conditionally safe, different threads can access different object simultaneously and access to shared data is protected from race conditions. not thread safe, data structures should not be accessed simultaneously by different threads

database concurrency controls, ensure that correct results for concurrent operations are generated. help prevent deadlocks in databases. acid test










ACID Model for Database Transactions:

database transaction requirements for developing reliable database systems; atomicity, each transaction is treated as a single unit, which either succeeds completely or fails completely. consistency, transaction can only bring the database from one valid state to another, preventing data corruption from an illegal transaction. isolation, ensures that concurrent execution of transactions leaves the database in the same state that would have been obtained if the transactions were executed sequentially. durability, once a transaction has been committed, it will remain committed even in the case of a system failure














