you need to manage vulnerabilities in all environments

the CVE database can help you evaluate and mitigate vulnerabilities 

this includes triaging and tracking vulnerabilities












Runtime Protection:

technology which embeds into an application or application runtime environment, examine requests at the application layer to detect attacks and misuse in real time

runtime application self protection (RASP) capabilities include unpack and inspect application requests, monitor and block application requests, protect against all classes of application attacks, pinpoint where a vulnerability exists, instrument application functions and report on usage.

implement a web application firewall (WAF) for web applications

utilize hardware protection including address space layout randomization (ASLR) and dynamic execution prevention (DEP)











Service Level Agreements (SLA):

one of an organizations primary contracting vehicles

a contract with indemnities; a commitment between a service provider and a client. a particular aspect of the service, quality, availability, and timely. responsibilities are agreed between the service provider and the service user and may cover performance, availability, and personnel

basic components of an SLA include but are not limited to type of service to be provided, the services desired by performance level, monitoring process and service level reporting, the steps for reporting issues with the service, response and issue resolution timeframe, repercussions for service provider not meeting its commitment











Service Level Objectives:

a key element of a service level agreement between a service provider and a customer

SLOs are agreed upon as a means of measuring the performance of the service provider

typically defined as a way of avoiding disputes between the two parties based on misunderstanding. example; the application will be available 99.95% of the time










