Provenance Versus Pedigree:

provenance, the documentation of where something comes from and the processes and methodologies by which it was produced

pedigree, includes not only the history but also the quality of something. include accuracy, correctness, timeliness, completeness, compliance with standards, and trustworthiness. an attribute of provenance











Third-part Software Security Pedigree:

requires due care and due diligence

security pedigree; the security lineage of an organization, system, or software

attributes that show pedigree; secure transfer, secure system sharing/interconnections, code repository security, build environment security, cryptographically hashed, digitally signed, right to audit










