Contractual Requirements:

for third-party security requirements to be enforceable, they must be contractually binding, mutually agreed upon (contract driven), have the appropriate level of transparency, measurable, and enforced

all contracting vehicles must make potential vendors aware of the security requirements, which should be; transparent, tied to business requirements (possibly to compliance), non-negotiable, and unambiguous













